// A shadow resolver whose return type is a UNION with a @weak client member is
// STILL a hard error (weak routing must not bypass any union gate and
// emit an artifact). A union with a @weak/CSE member is rejected even earlier than
// the shadow union gate: the docblock-level @outputType union check
// (`RelayResolverOutputTypeUnsupported`) fires first, so a weak union return never
// reaches the inline classification at all. Either way the result is a
// hard error and no artifact -- use an interface return instead.
